# ScalarForensic configuration
# Copy this file to .env and adjust to your environment.
# Environment variables already set in the shell take precedence over this file.

# --- Docker image directory (Docker Compose only, not read by the app) ---
# Docker Compose reads this from .env for variable substitution in docker-compose.yml.
# It controls which host directory is bind-mounted as /images inside the container.
# Setting it here ensures the correct path is used for BOTH `docker compose up`
# AND `docker compose run` without having to export it in the shell each time.
# SFN_IMAGES_DIR=/path/to/evidence/images

# --- Qdrant connection ---
# This project expects a running Qdrant server at the configured URL.
# For local development, start Qdrant before launching the app:
#   docker run --rm -p 6333:6333 qdrant/qdrant
SFN_QDRANT_URL=http://localhost:6333
# For remote instances the port must be explicit in the URL — qdrant-client defaults to
# :6333 otherwise, even over HTTPS. Use :443 for standard TLS endpoints:
#   SFN_QDRANT_URL=https://your-qdrant-host.example.com:443
# API key for remote Qdrant instances that require authentication (Qdrant Cloud etc.)
# Leave unset for unauthenticated / local instances.
# SFN_QDRANT_API_KEY=your-qdrant-api-key

# --- Collection name ---
# A single Qdrant collection holds all vector types (DINOv2 as "dino", SSCD as "sscd")
# using Qdrant's named-vector feature.  Both vectors live on the same point so that
# exact-hash, altered-copy and semantic queries share one data store.
SFN_COLLECTION=sfn

# --- Model identifiers ---
SFN_MODEL_DINO=models/dinov2-large
# SSCD checkpoint must exist on disk (download from the sscd-copy-detection releases page)
# For offline/portable use, place both models under models/ in the project root.
SFN_MODEL_SSCD=models/sscd_disc_mixup.torchscript.pt
# For offline/airgapped use, snapshot DINOv2 with the download script:
#   uv run python scripts/download_models.py --dino
# Then point here:
# SFN_MODEL_DINO=models/dinov2-large

# --- Image preprocessing ---
# DINOv2 input resolution in pixels (N×N crop after resize).  SSCD uses its own
# fixed 288 px crop regardless of this setting.
# 224 (default) — ImageNet convention; best throughput.
# 512           — closer to DINOv2's 518 px training resolution; higher fidelity
#                  for large, detail-rich images at ~26× more ViT attention cost.
# Note: changing this after indexing is incompatible with existing embeddings.
# sfn refuses to index against a mismatched collection (use --ignore-config-mismatch
# to override).  sfn-web does not block on this — Phase 2 only re-embeds queries
# and a normalize_size drift is caught at the next index run.
# SFN_NORMALIZE_SIZE=224

# SSCD spatial crops per image.
# 1 (default) — center crop only; matches SSCD training protocol.
# 5           — center + 4 corners; recommended for forensic use when evidence
#                images may have relevant content off-center (surveillance stills,
#                padded or watermarked images).  ~5× SSCD compute; halve
#                SFN_BATCH_SIZE or rely on auto-calibration.
# Note: changing this after indexing is incompatible with existing embeddings.
# sfn-web refuses to start and sfn refuses to index on mismatch — n_crops is the
# one Phase-2 setting whose drift silently corrupts query results.  Pass
# --ignore-config-mismatch to sfn to override (no override at web startup).
# SFN_SSCD_N_CROPS=1

# Pillow decompression-bomb pixel limit override.
# By default Pillow's built-in guard (128 MP) is left unchanged, preserving safety for
# untrusted inputs.  For trusted, high-resolution ingestion runs you can raise or remove it:
#   SFN_MAX_IMAGE_PIXELS=200000000   # allow up to 200 MP
#   SFN_MAX_IMAGE_PIXELS=none        # disable the guard entirely (also: disable / disabled)
# SFN_MAX_IMAGE_PIXELS=

# --- Video frame extraction ---
# SFN_VIDEO_FPS: frames extracted per second of video (default 1.0).
# Lower values reduce index size and processing time; raise for fast-moving content.
# SFN_VIDEO_FPS=1.0
#
# SFN_VIDEO_MAX_FRAMES: hard cap on frames extracted per video file (default 500, 0 = no cap).
# Protects against very long videos exhausting memory or taking impractical time to index.
# At 1 fps the default allows ~8 min of footage before the cap kicks in.
# SFN_VIDEO_MAX_FRAMES=500

# --- Pipeline tuning ---
# SFN_BATCH_SIZE: images processed per GPU batch.
# When unset (default), the CLI auto-calibrates on first run using a Michaelis-Menten
# saturation model and caches the result in data/sfn_batch_cache.json.  All subsequent
# runs (CLI and web) load the cached value automatically.  Set an explicit value to
# override the cache at any time.
# SFN_BATCH_SIZE=32
# Compute device: auto | cuda | cpu | mps
# On AMD ROCm, PyTorch exposes the GPU through the CUDA interface — both "auto"
# and "cuda" will use the ROCm/HIP backend. "auto" is recommended.
# For GPUs not natively supported by your ROCm version (e.g. using an RDNA 3
# card with a ROCm build that predates it), set HSA_OVERRIDE_GFX_VERSION in
# your shell to the closest supported architecture before running:
#   export HSA_OVERRIDE_GFX_VERSION=11.0.0   # gfx1100 as a stand-in
# gfx1201 (RX 9070 / 9070 XT) with ROCm 6.4 does NOT need this override.
SFN_DEVICE=auto

# --- Input directory ---
# Root of your evidence/image data on disk.  Must be set for the web UI to
# serve hit images and metadata — without it, all image previews and the
# SHA-256/MD5/dims panel will be blank (403 File serving is disabled).
# Also used as the default input for `sfn index` when no path argument is given.
# Can still be overridden by passing a positional argument on the command line.
# SFN_INPUT_DIR=/mnt/evidence/images

# --- Deduplication strategy ---
# hash     – skip images whose SHA-256 hash is already in the collection (default)
# filepath – skip images whose absolute path is already in the collection
# both     – skip images where EITHER the hash OR the path is already indexed
SFN_DUPLICATE_CHECK_MODE=hash

# --- EXIF metadata extraction ---
# When true, each indexed point will include two boolean fields:
#   exif         – whether the image contains any EXIF data
#   exif_geo_data – whether the image contains GPS/geolocation EXIF data
SFN_EXTRACT_EXIF=true

# --- Remote embeddings endpoint (optional, replaces local DINOv2/SSCD models) ---
# Set SFN_EMBEDDING_ENDPOINT to use any OpenAI-compatible POST /v1/embeddings server
# (e.g. Infinity, a custom FastAPI wrapper, etc.) instead of running models locally.
# Images are sent as base64 JPEG data-URIs in the "input" array.
#
# Required when endpoint is set:
#   SFN_EMBEDDING_MODEL  – model name to pass in the API request body
#   SFN_EMBEDDING_DIM    – embedding dimension the remote model produces
#
# Optional:
#   SFN_EMBEDDING_API_KEY – Bearer token if the endpoint requires authentication
#
# SFN_EMBEDDING_ENDPOINT=http://localhost:7997
# SFN_EMBEDDING_MODEL=clip-ViT-B-32
# SFN_EMBEDDING_DIM=512
# SFN_EMBEDDING_API_KEY=your-embedding-api-key

# --- Network policy ---
# By default ScalarForensic operates fully offline: the HuggingFace SDK is blocked
# from making any network requests (HF_HUB_OFFLINE=1 / TRANSFORMERS_OFFLINE=1 are set
# automatically).  Connections to SFN_QDRANT_URL and SFN_EMBEDDING_ENDPOINT are always
# allowed — they are explicit user-configured endpoints, not internet traffic.
#
# Set to true (or pass --allow-online to sfn / sfn-web) ONLY for first-time model
# downloads.  Once models are cached locally, revert to false (or leave it unset).
SFN_ALLOW_ONLINE=false

# --- Web UI vector visualization ---
# Maximum number of collection points fetched per model for the 3-D background
# visualization on the upload page.  Higher values produce a denser point cloud
# at the cost of a slower initial load (PCA projection runs server-side on startup).
# Set to 0 to disable the visualization entirely.
# SFN_VIZ_MAX_POINTS=5000

# --- Thumbnail cache ---
# 128×128 JPEG thumbnails are generated during `sfn index`, named by SHA-256
# hash, and served at /api/thumbnail/{sha256} for the hits list.
# Default: data/thumbnails (relative to CWD — created automatically on first use).
# Override with an absolute path, or set to empty to disable:
#   SFN_THUMBNAIL_DIR=          # disable
#   SFN_THUMBNAIL_DIR=/data/sfn-thumbnails   # custom path
# SFN_THUMBNAIL_SIZE=128

# --- Optional: HEIC/HEIF support ---
# Install pillow-heif to automatically enable .heic and .heif file scanning:
#   uv sync --group heif
# No configuration needed — support is enabled automatically when the package is present.
